entry.title: documentScan: Include protocol_type in ScannerInfo response
entry.content:
If a scanner supports multiple protocols, it can be discovered multiple

times. In a pure SANE world, these can be distinguished by parsing the

SANE device name. Since chrome.documentScan hides the original names

behind unguessable tokens, an extension cannot do this, so it ends up

with multiple scanner entries that are indistinguishable.



In order to let the extension distinguish these entries without

re-exposing the original connection string, lorgnette has added a

protocol_type field to its responses. This CL adds this field to the

mojo and idl representations and passes the value along from the lorgnette response all the way to the chrome.documentScan.getScannerList response.

entry.title: Feature to control low latency canvas overlay
entry.content:
Goal is add ways to allow experimenting with enabling low latency canvas

(both 2D and WebGL) on Android. "Enable" means in overlay and

single-buffered canvas.



There are existing Canvas2DImageChromium and WebGLImageChromium runtime

features which controls overlaying these types of canvases in general,

not just low latency ones. We do not intend on shipping this on Android

currently.



There is also existing kLowLatencyCanvas2dImageChromium base::Feature

which controls overlaying low latency 2D canvas even if

Canvas2DImageChromium is not enabled. This CL adds a similar one for

WebGL: kLowLatencyWebGLImageChromium. Will use these two to control

experiments for Android. Disable both of these at runtime for Android

WebView since WebView is not in consideration for low latency canvas

for this project.

entry.title: Event Timing - Handle modal dialog interference
entry.content:
* Previous undesired outcome: event timing could measure the arbitrarily

long user input waiting time on synchronous javascript modal dialogs

and report it as part of the presentation delay.

* Root cause: synchronous modal dialogs paused the event-damaged frame

to be presented until after user close the dialog.

* This CL address it by: treating modal dialogs showing as another way

of page responding and report the dialog showing timestamp as an

alternative end time for duration measurement to any events that was

interfered by the modal dialog in event timing.

entry.title: Shared Storage: Migrate database to track bytes used per origin
entry.content:
We migrate the shared storage SQLite database to version 5, which adds

a `num_bytes` column to the `per_origin_mapping` table. This will

track the total number of bytes stored in keys and values in the

`values_mapping` table by the associated origin.



We update several database methods in order to maintain the new

`num_bytes` column, and fix tests as necessary.



A follow-up CL (https://crrev.com/c/5280364) will add methods to query

the `num_bytes` column. At that point we will add more unit tests to

more thoroughly verify that the updates to database methods are working

as intended.



shared_storage_database_migrations.cc are executed only if a

`sql::Database` error occurs. To force database errors, we would

need to mock the `sql::Database` class, which currently doesn't

have any virtual methods.

entry.title: [PIX] Let the browser know if an invalid PIX code was detected
entry.content:
Before this patch, the FacilitatedPaymentsAgent in the renderer process

sent only a boolean that was true when a valid PIX was found. Not

running PIX code detection, absence of PIX code, or an invalid PIX code

resulted in the boolean "false".



The boolean made it hard to distinguish whether Chrome is failing to

find a PIX code or is failing to validate it, which is possible when a

page contains the indicator string "0014br.gov.bcb.pix", but the rest of

the string does not follow a valid PIX code format.



This patch changes the mojom IPC to return an enum with four possible

values instead of the existing boolean.



After this patch, the FacilitatedPaymentsAgent in the renderer process

sends an enum with one of the following four values:

1) PIX code detection was not run.

2) No PIX code was found.

3) An invalid PIX code was found.

4) A valid PIX code was found.



Bug: 324765365
